context.description:
The `ProtobufBuild` operator takes in a tuple of the type generated by `spl-schema-from-protobuf` script and converts it into a serialized Protobuf record.
The output is a blob data type. The operator will find the first blob data type field in the output port schema and use it as the field to contain the serialized record.

The `protoMessage` parameter takes in the fully-qualified message name in the Protobuf schema (my.package.MyMessage).
The `protoDirectory` parameter takes in the path (relative to application directory or absolute) to the directory containing the Protobuf files.
The `protoRootFile` parameter takes in the path (relative to the `protoDirectory`) for the root Protobuf file to be processed. The operator will also include any files imported from this root file.

+ Examples

# Examples

    stream<blob record> serializedRecords = ProtobufBuild(myMessages) {
        param
            protoMessage: "my.package.MyMessage";
            protoDirectory: "path/to/protobuf/files";
            protoRootFile: "nested/path/MyMessage.proto";
    }
